  "description": "You survived the crisis. Now comes the long, unglamorous work of healing.",
  "content": "The acute crisis has passed, but you're left with the aftermath—the relationships damaged, the time lost, the person you used to be who no longer exists. Recovery isn't dramatic or linear. It's showing up to therapy. It's taking medication. It's rebuilding routines one small habit at a time. It's forgiving yourself for things you did or didn't do during the worst of it. You're learning that survival was just the first step. Now comes the harder work of actually living again.",
