      "text": "Take recovery slowly and seriously",
      "description": "This isn't a race. Heal at your own pace.",
      "resultText": "You commit to the unsexy work of genuine recovery. You show up for appointments. You practice coping skills. You rest when you need to, push when you can, and try to distinguish between the two. Some days are better than others. Progress isn't linear. But when you look back over months, you can see real change. You're not who you were before the crisis—but you're becoming someone you can live with being.",
